{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846713265,"sessionID":"ses_28749eaf6ffebPa8vhmVB5f8vi","part":{"id":"prt_d78b66048001r8sTmx1b89XTjl","messageID":"msg_d78b64fa0001lv7sIQAm3b7eIR","sessionID":"ses_28749eaf6ffebPa8vhmVB5f8vi","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-5cb7a889994e4b1ebc77a58431434895","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: The WorkloadManager package provides the HTTP service framework for managing AgentCube sandbox lifecycles on Kubernetes. It orchestrates sandbox creation, deletion, garbage collection, and health monitoring through a layered architecture combining Kubernetes dynamic client operations with an in-memory store for session tracking.\n14: \n15: ## Design\n16: \n17: ### Architecture\n18: \n19: ```\n20: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n21: │                          HTTPServer                                  │\n22: │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────────┐ │\n23: │  │   Router    │  │ Middleware   │  │         Handlers            │ │\n24: │  │  (chi/v5)   │  │ Recovery     │  │ DeletionHandler             │ │\n25: │  │             │  │ Logging      │  │ HealthHandler               │ │\n26: │  │             │  │ CORS         │  │ HandlerFuncAdapter          │ │\n27: │  └─────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └─────────────────────────────┘ │\n28: │                               │                                      │\n29: │  ┌────────────────────────────┴───────────────────────────────────┐ │\n30: │  │                    SandboxLifecycleManager                       │ │\n31: │  │  - DeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID)                                 │ │\n32: │  │  - ForceDeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID)                            │ │\n33: │  │  - IsExpired(sandbox)                                            │ │\n34: │  │  - IsIdleExpired(sandbox, timeout)                               │ │\n35: │  │  - GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID)                                    │ │\n36: │  │  - UpdateSandboxStatus(ctx, sessionID, status)                  │ │\n37: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n38: │                               │                                      │\n39: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────┐│\n40: │  │ GarbageCollector │  │   K8sClient  │  │       MemoryStore       ││\n41: │  │ - runLoop()      │  │ dynamicClient│  │ - StoreSandbox()        ││\n42: │  │ - runOnce()      │  │ coreClient   │  │ - GetSandboxBySessionID ││\n43: │  │ - Start/Stop     │  │ podLister    │  │ - UpdateSandbox()       ││\n44: │  │                  │  │ informerFact │  │ - DeleteSandboxBySession││\n45: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────┘  │ - ListExpiredSandboxes  ││\n46: │                        ┌──────────────┐  │ - ListInactiveSandboxes ││\n47: │                        │  Informers   │  └─────────────────────────┘│\n48: │                        │ factory      │                              │\n49: │                        │ Start/Wait   │                              │\n50: │                        └──────────────┘                              │\n51: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n52: ```\n53: \n54: **Component Responsibilities:**\n55: \n56: | Component | Responsibility |\n57: |-----------|---------------|\n58: | `HTTPServer` | HTTP lifecycle management, graceful shutdown, handler registration |\n59: | `Router` | Chi router wrapper for route registration |\n60: | `Middleware` | Recovery, logging, CORS handling for all requests |\n61: | `Handlers` | HTTP endpoint implementation for sandbox operations |\n62: | `SandboxLifecycleManager` | Core sandbox lifecycle orchestration (create/delete/status) |\n63: | `GarbageCollector` | Background cleanup of expired/idle sandboxes |\n64: | `K8sClient` | Kubernetes client wrapper with dynamic/client-go/informers |\n65: | `Informers` | SharedInformerFactory for pod watching |\n66: | `MemoryStore` | In-memory session tracking with expiration indices |\n67: | `ClientCache` | Token-scoped dynamic client caching for multi-tenant access |\n68: \n69: ### Dependencies\n70: \n71: | Package | Purpose |\n72: |---------|---------|\n73: | `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` | HTTP routing |\n74: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Core Kubernetes client |\n75: | `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic` | Dynamic client for CRD operations |\n76: | `k8s.io/client-go/informers` | SharedInformerFactory for caching |\n77: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` | K8s API error handling |\n78: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Controller utilities |\n79: \n80: ## Data Structures\n81: \n82: ### Core Types\n83: \n84: ```go\n85: type SandboxInfo struct {\n86:     Kind               string              // AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter/Sandbox/SandboxClaim\n87:     SandboxID          string              // Unique sandbox identifier\n88:     SandboxNamespace   string              // K8s namespace\n89:     SandboxName        string              // K8s resource name\n90:     Name               string              // Runtime name\n91:     SessionID          string              // Session identifier (primary key)\n92:     CreatedAt          time.Time           // Creation timestamp\n93:     ExpiresAt          time.Time           // Expiration timestamp\n94:     Status             string              // Current status\n95:     EntryPoints        []SandboxEntryPoint // Network entry points\n96:     UserToken          string              // User authentication token\n97:     ServiceAccount     string              // K8s service account\n98:     ServiceAccountName string              // Service account name\n99:     LastActivity       time.Time           // Last activity timestamp\n100: }\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ### Error Types\n104: \n105: ```go\n106: type ValidationError struct {\n107:     Field  string\n108:     Reason string\n109: }\n110: \n111: type NotFoundError struct {\n112:     Resource string\n113:     Name     string\n114: }\n115: \n116: type InternalError struct {\n117:     Err error\n118: }\n119: \n120: type ServiceUnavailableError struct {\n121:     Dependency string\n122: }\n123: \n124: type ConflictError struct {\n125:     Resource string\n126:     Err      error\n127: }\n128: ```\n129: \n130: ### Configuration Types\n131: \n132: ```go\n133: type Config struct {\n134:     Addr            string        // \":8080\"\n135:     ReadTimeout     time.Duration // 15s\n136:     WriteTimeout    time.Duration // 15s\n137:     IdleTimeout     time.Duration // 60s\n138:     ShutdownTimeout time.Duration // 30s\n139:     EnableHealthz   bool\n140:     EnableReadyz    bool\n141: }\n142: \n143: type LifecycleConfig struct {\n144:     DefaultTTL          time.Duration // 8h\n145:     DefaultIdleTimeout  time.Duration // 15m\n146:     DefaultMaxDuration  time.Duration // 8h\n147:     GCInterval          time.Duration // 2m\n148:     GCOnceTimeout       time.Duration // 2m\n149:     DeletionGracePeriod int64         // 0\n150:     DeletionTimeout     time.Duration // 30s\n151: }\n152: ```\n153: \n154: ### Constants and GVR\n155: \n156: ```go\n157: const (\n158:     DefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour\n159:     DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n160:     DefaultMaxSessionDuration = 8 * time.Hour\n161:     SandboxCreationTimeout    = 2 * time.Minute\n162:     SandboxDeleteTimeout      = 30 * time.Second\n163:     InformerSyncTimeout       = 1 * time.Minute\n164:     GarbageCollectorInterval  = 2 * time.Minute\n165:     GCBatchSize               = 16\n166: )\n167: \n168: var SandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n169:     Group:    \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n170:     Version:  \"v1alpha1\",\n171:     Resource: \"sandboxes\",\n172: }\n173: \n174: var SandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n175:     Group:    \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\",\n176:     Version:  \"v1alpha1\",\n177:     Resource: \"sandboxclaims\",\n178: }\n179: ```\n180: \n181: ### Labels and Annotations\n182: \n183: ```go\n184: const (\n185:     LabelKeySessionID    = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"\n186:     LabelKeyWorkloadName = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"\n187:     LabelKeySandboxName  = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"\n188:     LabelKeyManagedBy    = \"managed-by\"\n189:     ManagedByValue       = \"agentcube-workload-manager\"\n190:     \n191:     AnnotationKeyIdleTimeout = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"\n192:     AnnotationKeyPodName     = \"agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name\"\n193: )\n194: ```\n195: \n196: ## API Endpoints\n197: \n198: ### Sandbox Deletion\n199: \n200: | Method | Path | Description |\n201: |--------|------|-------------|\n202: | DELETE | `/v1/agent-runtime/sessions/{sessionId}` | Delete AgentRuntime sandbox |\n203: | DELETE | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{sessionId}` | Delete CodeInterpreter sandbox |\n204: \n205: **Request:**\n206: - `sessionId` (path parameter) - Required\n207: - `force` (optional) - Force deletion with gracePeriod=0\n208: - `gracePeriodSeconds` (optional) - Deletion grace period\n209: \n210: **Response (200):**\n211: ```json\n212: {\n213:     \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n214:     \"status\": \"deleted\"\n215: }\n216: ```\n217: \n218: **Response (404):**\n219: ```json\n220: {\n221:     \"sessionId\": \"session-123\",\n222:     \"status\": \"not_found\",\n223:     \"message\": \"not found: sandbox/session-123\"\n224: }\n225: ```\n226: \n227: ### Health Endpoints\n228: \n229: | Method | Path | Description |\n230: |--------|------|-------------|\n231: | GET | `/healthz` | Basic health check |\n232: | GET | `/readyz` | Readiness check (informers sync) |\n233: \n234: ## Error Handling\n235: \n236: ### Error Classification\n237: \n238: | Error Type | HTTP Status | Code |\n239: |------------|-------------|------|\n240: | `ValidationError` | 400 | VALIDATION_ERROR |\n241: | `NotFoundError` | 404 | NOT_FOUND |\n242: | `ServiceUnavailableError` | 503 | SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE |\n243: | `ConflictError` | 409 | (via K8s API) |\n244: | `InternalError` | 500 | INTERNAL_ERROR |\n245: \n246: ### HandleError Function\n247: \n248: ```go\n249: func HandleError(w http.ResponseWriter, _ *http.Request, err error) {\n250:     w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n251:     \n252:     var resp ErrorResponse\n253:     var status int\n254:     \n255:     switch e := err.(type) {\n256:     case *ValidationError:\n257:         status = http.StatusBadRequest\n258:         resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"VALIDATION_ERROR\", Message: \"Invalid request parameter\", ...}\n259:     case *NotFoundError:\n260:         status = http.StatusNotFound\n261:         resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"NOT_FOUND\", Message: e.Error()}\n262:     case *ServiceUnavailableError:\n263:         status = http.StatusServiceUnavailable\n264:         resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\", ...}\n265:     case *InternalError:\n266:         status = http.StatusInternalServerError\n267:         resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", Message: \"Unexpected server error\"}\n268:     default:\n269:         status = http.StatusInternalServerError\n270:         resp = ErrorResponse{Code: \"INTERNAL_ERROR\", Message: \"Unexpected server error\"}\n271:     }\n272:     \n273:     w.WriteHeader(status)\n274:     json.NewEncoder(w).Encode(resp)\n275: }\n276: ```\n277: \n278: ### K8s API Error Handling\n279: \n280: ```go\n281: func handleDeleteError(err error) error {\n282:     if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n283:         return nil  // Already deleted, success\n284:     }\n285:     if apierrors.IsConflict(err) {\n286:         return &ConflictError{Resource: \"sandbox\", Err: err}\n287:     }\n288:     return &InternalError{Err: err}\n289: }\n290: ```\n291: \n292: ## Testing Strategy\n293: \n294: ### Test Patterns\n295: \n296: 1. **Unit Tests** - Each component tested independently with mocks\n297: 2. **Fake K8s Clients** - `dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient`, `fake.NewSimpleClientset`\n298: 3. **Mock Logger** - Simple struct capturing Info/Error calls\n299: 4. **Test Informer Factory** - `NewTestInformerFactory` for controlled sync\n300: \n301: ### Test Helpers\n302: \n303: ```go\n304: type mockLogger struct {\n305:     infoCalls  []string\n306:     errorCalls []string\n307: }\n308: \n309: func (l *mockLogger) Info(msg string, args ...any) {\n310:     l.infoCalls = append(l.infoCalls, msg)\n311: }\n312: \n313: func (l *mockLogger) Error(msg string, args ...any) {\n314:     l.errorCalls = append(l.errorCalls, msg)\n315: }\n316: \n317: func NewTestInformerFactory(client kubernetes.Interface) informers.SharedInformerFactory {\n318:     return informers.NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(client, time.Minute)\n319: }\n320: ```\n321: \n322: ### Test Coverage Areas\n323: \n324: | File | Test Coverage |\n325: |------|---------------|\n326: | `lifecycle_test.go` | DeleteSandbox, ForceDeleteSandbox, IsExpired, IsIdleExpired, GetSandbox, UpdateSandboxStatus |\n327: | `k8s_client_test.go` | NewK8sClient, StartInformers, WaitForCacheSync, PodLister, ClientCache |\n328: | `store_test.go` | StoreSandbox, GetSandboxBySessionID, UpdateSandbox, DeleteSandbox, ListExpired/Inactive |\n329: | `garbage_collector_test.go` | runOnce, Start/Stop, idle timeout behavior |\n330: | `handlers/sandbox_delete_test.go` | HTTP deletion endpoints, error handling |\n331: | `server_test.go` | Start/Stop, GracefulShutdown, handler registration |\n332: \n333: ### Integration Test Strategy\n334: \n335: ```go\n336: func TestIntegration_ServerLifecycle(t *testing.T) {\n337:     scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n338:     dynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(scheme)\n339:     fakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n340:     informerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n341:     \n342:     k8sClient := &K8sClient{\n343:         dynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n344:         coreClient:      fakeClient,\n345:         informerFactory: informerFactory,\n346:     }\n347:     \n348:     store := NewMemoryStore()\n349:     logger := &mockLogger{}\n350:     cfg := DefaultConfig()\n351:     \n352:     server := NewHTTPServerWithClients(cfg, logger, k8sClient, store)\n353:     \n354:     // Register handlers, start server, verify endpoints\n355: }\n356: ```\n357: \n358: ## Validation Checklist\n359: \n360: - [x] HTTPServer graceful shutdown with context timeout\n361: - [x] K8sClient with dynamic/client-go/informers integration\n362: - [x] MemoryStore with expiration and activity indices\n363: - [x] GarbageCollector background cleanup loop\n364: - [x] SandboxLifecycleManager handles Sandbox + SandboxClaim deletion\n365: - [x] Error classification with structured JSON responses\n366: - [x] DeletionReason enum for tracking cleanup triggers\n367: - [x] ClientCache for multi-tenant token-scoped clients\n368: - [x] Chi router with middleware chain (Recovery → Logging → CORS)\n369: \n370: ## Open Questions\n371: \n372: - Q: Should Store interface support persistent backend (Redis/etcd)?\n373:   - A: MemoryStore is current implementation; Store interface allows future extension\n374: \n375: - Q: Should AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter informers watch CR status changes?\n376:   - A: Current implementation uses Pod informers; CR informers can be added via client-go generated informers\n377: \n378: - Q: Should GarbageCollector emit metrics for deletion counts/reasons?\n379:   - A: Not implemented yet; can be added via Prometheus integration\n380: \n381: ## References\n382: \n383: - `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/` - Generated client-go for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n384: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go` - AgentRuntime CRD definition\n385: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` - CodeInterpreter CRD definition\n386: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` - Shared types, labels, annotations, conditions\n387: - `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` - SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response\n388: - `deployment/client-go.md` - Client-go library documentation\n\n(End of file - total 388 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe WorkloadManager package provides the HTTP service framework for managing AgentCube sandbox lifecycles on Kubernetes. It orchestrates sandbox creation, deletion, garbage collection, and health monitoring through a layered architecture combining Kubernetes dynamic client operations with an in-memory store for session tracking.\n\n## Design\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/design.md","time":{"start":1775846713246,"end":1775846713262}}}}
